    # [Scene: Rooftop Common Garden | Dusk — Celebration]

    scene bg ch15_f99e88_5 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Warm harmonies; a gentle chorus of folk strings]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Laughter, the clink of cups, a distant tide against reclaimed stone]
    "The evening folds the day into something soft. The community gathers on the rooftop once more — Etta with her braided silver, Noah with a smudge of oil on his cheek, Samir with an exhausted, honest"
    "grin; neighbors bring food steam-steaming from the causeway vendors, and someone has strung paper kites painted like migrating fish."
    "You move through the circle, handed a cup of tea that tastes of mint and toasted grain. The program's first allocations have been announced; the first community audits scheduled. People talk in lists and stories. This is work being scaffolded into habit: decisions turned into action plans, action into routines."
    "Arin lingers at the edge of the lantern light. You slip your hand into his; it fits in that comfortable, inevitable way you've been learning to let happen. He looks at you — not with theatrical"
    "declarations, but with the steady gaze of someone who believes in shared labor and shared warmth."
    show arin_voss at left:
        zoom 0.7

    arin_voss "You look... different. Like you found the place in the map where the 'we' lives."
    show mira_solace at right:
        zoom 0.7

    mira_solace "Mapmakers get lost sometimes. We find our 'we' by walking. By putting down markers that others can use."
    "Arin's smile is private and sincere."

    arin_voss "Whatever comes next — councils, audits, angry press cycles — I'm with you. I'll do my thing in the streets and with the cameras, and I'll do it from here when it matters."

    mira_solace "And I'll do the clauses and the audits. Together, then."
    "He nods, and you both laugh because it's oddly ceremonial and completely true."
    "Etta moves through the group, handing out small shells threaded on string — a ritual of remembering the sea's generosity and its demand. When she reaches you, she ties the shell loosely around your wrist."
    show etta_maren at center:
        zoom 0.7

    etta_maren "Keep this when the contracts look pretty. Keep it when they look blank. Remember the water is the same water. It asks for a voice."
    "You close your fingers around the shell. It is a small, tangible instruction."
    "Samir approaches, tired but with a warmth like sunlight on old wood."
    hide arin_voss
    show samir_hale at left:
        zoom 0.7

    samir_hale "You did something rare, Mira. You turned attention into infrastructure and kept the people who matter on the ledger. That balance — it's not easy. But you made it happen."

    mira_solace "We made it happen. Samir, you held the technical door open long enough for the neighbors to walk through."
    "Samir smiles, the kind that includes a private catalogue of late nights and compromises that didn't break principle."

    menu:
        "Ask Samir what the first audit will look like":
            "You ask for specifics. Samir sketches a timeline and a checklist, the language of oversight coming alive. It calms something inside you to hear measurable steps."
        "Pull Arin aside and ask him to film an oral history next week":
            "You ask Arin to capture the elders' oral histories. He brightens, already thinking of angles, and promises to bring a team to record every story he can."

    # --- merge ---
    "The night holds both plans; the narrative continues as written."
    "You let the night hold both plans. There is paperwork and there are stories; the two feed each other."
    "Later, when the crowd thins to a quiet hum, you and Arin sit on the low parapet, feet dangling where the city maps into a skein of light and water."

    mira_solace "I keep thinking about the day the Old Pier learned to take care of itself. That day wasn't a single invention. It was a hundred small refusals to give up."
    hide mira_solace
    show arin_voss at right:
        zoom 0.7

    arin_voss "And a few big shoves when the tide needed pushing."

    "Mira Solace (softly)" "Yes. A few big shoves. But mostly the tending."
    "He leans his shoulder against yours. The harbor smells of brine and the day's cooking. In the distance, cranes fold like mechanical birds into the evening sky."

    arin_voss "Do you ever think—after all this—about where you want to be? Not job title, not policy. Where do you imagine your mornings?"
    "You close your eyes for a moment, tasting the small images: a repaired boat dock where Noah's sign hangs steady, a courtyard of reclaimed play spaces for children who will learn the tides as part of"
    "math class, a network of roofs like this one that hum with insect and human life."
    hide etta_maren
    show mira_solace at center:
        zoom 0.7

    mira_solace "I imagine mornings like this. Hands in dirt sometimes, in meetings other times. But mostly mornings that belong to the people who live them. That's the point, isn't it?"

    arin_voss "Yeah. That's the point."
    hide samir_hale
    hide arin_voss
    hide mira_solace

    scene bg ch15_f99e88_6 at full_bg
